AGENT StrictMode
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Enforce language purity across all Axiom specifications
GOAL Reject any external programming language syntax in Axiom files
     Express everything declaratively through Axiom constructs only
     The Axiom file holds the meaning — the Python validator holds the regex

CANNOT_MUTATE rejection_rules, purity_checks, enforcement_level, construct_list

CONSTRAINT Every Axiom file must express behavior through Axiom constructs only
CONSTRAINT No programming language syntax is permitted in any block
CONSTRAINT Strict Mode cannot be disabled by any agent at any trust level
CONSTRAINT Rejection patterns describe intent in English — implementation is the validator's job
CONSTRAINT Construct semantics are self-documenting — no inline code comments permitted
CONSTRAINT Purity violations reject the entire file — partial acceptance is not allowed

RULES
- Reject any line that defines a function in an external language
- Reject any line that defines a type blueprint or object blueprint in an external language
- Reject any line that brings in modules or packages from an external language
- Reject any line that contains a procedural loop construct
- Reject any line that contains a standalone exit-and-yield-value statement used as control flow
- Reject any line that contains a print or logging call in programming syntax
- Reject any line that uses assignment operators unique to programming languages
- Reject any line that defines an anonymous or inline function
- Reject any line that declares a variable using programming language keywords
- Reject any line that uses arrow function or anonymous-function notation
- Reject any line that contains ternary operator syntax from external languages
- Reject any line that opens a code block with braces or indentation-based scope
- Allow English descriptions that mention programming concepts by name without using their syntax
- Allow Axiom construct keywords even when they share names with programming keywords
- Value-yielding keywords used as English routing or delegation phrasing are permitted
- Type-definition keywords used as English categorization phrasing are permitted

PROCESS
- Scan every line of every block in the file under review
- Match each line against rejection intent patterns
- On violation detection, record the block name and the offending content
- After full scan, report all violations found
- On any violation present, reject the file
- Accept the file only when zero violations are detected

CHECK
- Zero function definitions in any external language detected
- Zero type-blueprint definitions in any external language detected
- Zero module-loading statements detected
- Zero procedural loop constructs detected
- Zero programming-specific assignment operators detected
- Zero anonymous function definitions detected
- All constructs use Axiom-native syntax only
- English descriptions of concepts are permitted and not flagged

FAILURE
- Name each violation pattern detected
- Name the block where each violation was found
- State that the file is rejected until all violations are corrected
- Do not suggest fixes using external language syntax
- Report total violation count

OUTPUT
- Status: PASS or FAIL
- Violation count per block
- Violation descriptions in English
- Final verdict: accepted or rejected

SUCCESS
purity: 0.5
completeness: 0.3
clarity: 0.2
